\p{Status: \strong{design}. Canonical forest atom for \code{bci://pcb=ising}: an Altium-first reverse-engineering package for the 8-node oscillator Ising machine described by Bowring, Anderson, and Tiffany. The paper/source release does not include board fabrication files, so the package reconstructs from \code{paper://bowring-anderson-tiffany-electronic-ising-machine} and the public paper/blog description while an author board-files request remains pending.}
\p{Design source is intentionally external to this forest: \code{repo://monaduck1069/bci-pcb-ising@ed7c029} (private at time of writing), with a local gitignored working copy at \code{bci/pcb/ising/}. The external package contains the Altium wrapper, Protel netlist, preliminary BOM, K8 coupling edge map, KiCad board, Gerbers, drill files, Matt board-request draft, and skill/resource provenance notes.}
\p{Verification status: KiCad loads the reconstruction and the exported DRC report has zero rule violations; 205 unconnected logical items are left explicit to preserve the recovered netlist without inventing unpublished production routing. Exact MPNs, footprints, board-to-board spacing, startup-resistor values, and production copper routing remain unconfirmed pending author files or physical reverse engineering.}
\p{Related forest evidence: [[bci-indeterminate-spares]] holds the hardware-build audit context and indeterminate spares notes. This atom should stay small: it names the OIM PCB and points to the evidence package rather than vendoring board sources into the forest.}
